Foreign companies withdraw employees
Companies are suspending operations all over the resource-rich countries.
Foreign companies such as the steel company Arcelor Mittal are withdrawing their employees, and several international airlines are no longer flying to the affected regions.
Local traders and farmers also react: Few merchants still leave their home towns to get supplies.
In some areas in Sierra Leone and Liberia, which are quarantined, the cocoa and coffee beans that are important for export are rotting in the fields.
Farmers do not dare to leave their homes for harvest.
Food is scarce
“People are going to travel less and less,” says Phillipe De Vreyer, Parisian expert on the economy of West Africa.
The man, for example, who usually goes to the market and sells his vegetables, prefers to stay at home.
